1,MCQ,Which nmap flag is used to scan specifically for the default MQTT port?,-p 8080,-p 1883,-p 443,-p 21,Option B,MQTT natively operates on TCP port 1883.
2,MCQ,How can an attacker discover hidden topics on a misconfigured MQTT broker?,SQL Injection,Subscribing to #,Path Traversal,ARP Spoofing,Option B,The # wildcard allows a subscriber to see all messages published to all topics if ACLs permit it.
3,MCQ,What vulnerability allowed the rogue payload injection?,Buffer Overflow,XSS,Misconfigured ACLs,Weak Passwords,Option C,Access Control Lists (ACLs) restrict who can publish/subscribe. Weak ACLs allow unauthorized data injection.
